BUTLER: He was the primary resident of this domicile. I had served him for many orbital periods.

YOU: What was he like?

BUTLER: He was kind, wise, and noble. Any positive adjective you can think of would suitably describe some aspect of his personality. His death is a tragedy of the highest order.

